<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-843-261  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 843 261.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  March 27 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NEC HE to follow Nintendo and Sega in Korea. (NEC HomeElectronics, Sega Enterprises)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   NEC Home Electronics Ltd. (marketing).andO;Product:   NEC PCEngine Shuttle (Video game) (marketing).andO;Topic:     Computer industryVideo gamesMarket EntryKoreaPlanning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEC HE TO FOLLOW NINTENDO AND SEGA IN KOREA TOKYO, JAPAN, 1990 MAR 20 (NB) --Following Nintendo and Sega Enterprises, NEC Home Electronics (HE) willlaunch its video game machine into the Korean market.andM;To start, NEC HE will export its PCEngine Shuttle through Korea-based DaewooElectronics starting in April.andP;  NEC HE is planning to price the video gamemachine at 150,000 won ($210) per unit, and initially release 15 gamecartridge titles.andP;  The number of titles should increase with alliances withKorean software houses.andP;  NEC HE intends to export 100,000 units for the firstyear.andM;Furthermore, NEC HE will export CoreGrafx, and SuperGrafx, more sophisticatedversions of Shuttle, in the near future.andM;In the Korean video game market, Nintendo is already selling its NintendoEntertainment System in a tie-up with Hyundai Corporation, which occurred inOctober of last year.andP;  Nintendo is scheduled to ship 300,000 units this year.andO;Also, Sega Enterprises will launch its 16-bit MegaDrive in cooperation withSam Sung Electronics next month.andM;Video games are increasing in popularity in Korea -- the the market isgrowing annually by 50 percent.andP;  Analysts project that video game machinesales will reach more than half million units this year.andM;Some 1.5 million units of the PCEngine have been sold in Japan and 300,000units in the U.S.A.andP;  to date.andP;  NEC HE is considering whether to launch thegame product into Europe, and finally distribute it worldwide.andM;(Ken Takahashi/19900322/Press Contact: NEC Home Electronics, 03-454-1789)</TEXT></DOC>